item.title: Duplicate identifier error
item.dc:creator: @inferno inferno
item.description:
@inferno wrote:

[quote=“picnic101, post:3, topic:9789”]in every script there si this error so i dont think it is just 1 script
Line 43: [Error] (14377:1): Duplicate identifier ‘Label1’ in script C:\Program Files\SCAR 2.03\Scripts\more scripts\scripts\1337_Fighter.scar
Line 66: [Error] (14640:1): Duplicate identifier ‘Label1’ in script C:\Program Files\SCAR 2.03\Scripts\high alcer phm100.scar
Line 44: [Error] (14378:1): Unknown identifier ‘FindFrog’ in script C:\Program Files\SCAR 2.03\Scripts\more scripts\scripts\Al kida gurd killer.scar
Line 447: [Error] (14597:1): Unknown identifier ‘Brightness’ in script C:\Program Files\SCAR 2.03\Scripts\more scripts\scripts\Inferno’s Varrock Smither.scar
there are some scripts =/[/quote]

Duplicate Identifier errors -> re-name it (like Home’s example above)

Unknown Identifier -> Srl has been updated and changed since the script was last updated meaning some procedures/functions have been deleted or re-named. Find out the new name (from the include) and replace it/delete it (in the script) or ask the scripter to update the script.
